# Architecture decisions

| Decision          | Value                                                |
|-------------------|------------------------------------------------------|
| Language          | <e.g. Python 3.12 / TypeScript / Rust 1.79>           |
| Runtime           | <e.g. CPython / Node.js 22 / native binary>           |
| Package manager   | <e.g. uv / pnpm / cargo / go modules>                 |
| Test runner       | <e.g. pytest / vitest / cargo test>                   |
| Formatter         | <e.g. ruff format / prettier / rustfmt>               |
| CI provider       | <e.g. GitHub Actions / GitLab CI / none>              |
| License           | <e.g. MIT / Apache-2.0 / proprietary>                 |
| Deploy target     | <e.g. Docker image / PyPI / npm / standalone binary>  |

# Phase 1: Architecture decisions

- [ ] Confirm the Architecture decisions table above with the user
- [ ] Write `{{paths_architecture_doc}}` stub describing intended layout

> ✋ Commit point: `chore: record architecture decisions`
> Verification before commit: `{{verify_format}}` clean, `{{verify_test}}` green.

> 🛑 New session boundary

# Phase 2: Directory skeleton + manifest

- [ ] Create `src/` and `tests/` (or language-appropriate equivalents)
- [ ] Create the language manifest (`pyproject.toml` / `package.json` / `Cargo.toml` / ...)
- [ ] Create `.gitignore` appropriate for the language
- [ ] Replace stub README with a proper project README skeleton

> ✋ Commit point: `chore: initialize project skeleton`
> Verification before commit: `{{verify_format}}` clean, `{{verify_test}}` green.

> 🛑 New session boundary

# Phase 3: First runnable module + verify wiring

- [ ] Implement a trivial entry point (e.g. main function that prints a hello)
- [ ] Add one passing test that exercises the entry point
- [ ] Confirm `{{verify_format}}` and `{{verify_test}}` actually execute successfully
- [ ] If the preset commands don't match reality, update `harness.config.toml` `[verify]` to the real commands

> ✋ Commit point: `feat: first runnable module`
> Verification before commit: `{{verify_format}}` clean, `{{verify_test}}` green.

> 🛑 New session boundary

# Phase 4: CONTRIBUTING fill + CI + scaffold close-out

- [ ] Walk user through each `🛠 TODO (project maintainers)` block in `CONTRIBUTING.md`:
      detect candidates from manifest/CI/formatter configs, present options,
      confirm with user, write confirmed content, delete the callout line
- [ ] Add a CI workflow that runs `{{verify_format_check}}` and `{{verify_test}}`
      on every push (or note "no CI" if the user opted out in Phase 1 decisions)
- [ ] **Remove `.harness/SCAFFOLD-PENDING`** to flip the project back to normal triage

> ✋ Commit point: `chore: complete project scaffold`
> Verification before commit: `{{verify_format}}` clean, `{{verify_test}}` green.

> 🛑 New session boundary
